---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Lead from "../../components/Lead.astro";
import StepNav from "../../components/StepNav.astro";
---

<Base
  title="You have a nervous system"
  description="Step one of the path: you have a nervous system, and it's quietly shaping how every moment feels."
  crumbs={[
    { label: "start here", href: "start/" },
  ]}
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl">You have a nervous system.</h1>
  <Lead>
    Right now, under everything you're thinking about, your nervous system is
    doing its constant job: checking whether you're safe, and setting the
    background tone of the moment accordingly. You don't decide this
    consciously. It's been running since before you had words.
  </Lead>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Most of us were never told this part plainly, so here it is: a large
      amount of how you feel — calm or on edge, open or braced, rested or
      wired — isn't really about willpower or attitude. It's your nervous
      system's read on the situation, happening faster than thought.
    </p>
    <p>
      That's not a flaw or a diagnosis. It's how bodies work. And it's oddly
      good news, because it means "just think positive" was never going to be
      the whole answer — and it isn't your fault that it wasn't enough.
    </p>
    <p>
      The rest of this short path is about getting familiar with that system:
      what its different states feel like, how they move through a normal day,
      and how — slowly — a stuck pattern can begin to change.
    </p>
  </div>

  <StepNav step={1} />
</Base>
